{
  "doc_id": "40513",
  "text": "Obesity and insulin resistance is associated with chronic systemic inflammation caused by activation of the intrinsic immune systems in organs and the macrophages that infiltrate them [CITATION_1] . The most prominent pro-inflammatory mediators involved in this inflammation are TNF and IL-6 that originate from: 1) macrophages in adipose tissue and the liver [CITATION_2] , 2) the adipocytes themselves [CITATION_3] , and, 3) several other cytokine synthesising tissues in the body [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] .",
